ls zweisprachig und ermöglicht gemeinsam mit der zweisprachigen Präsentation der Werke von Dictys und Dares einen neuen Zugang zu ‚alternativen Geschichten‘ von Troja.  aThe Trojan War is the subject of Homer’s Iliad, but there have also been ‘alternative accounts’ handed down since Antiquity. The Latin authors Dictys and Dares claimed to offer eyewitness accounts, asserting that they provided an authentic version of history. Since the Iliad was not read during the Middle Ages due to the poor knowledge of Greek, these two works have taken on a major significance for the reception of the events.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aTrojan WarvEarly works to 1800. 4aDares. 4aDictys. 4aHomer. 4aTroja. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aDares.  aDictys.  aHomer.  aTroy.1 aBrodersen, Kai, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDares, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311062013940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311062168640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110621686423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110621686.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019